# ZPC — Structured Project Memory

This project uses Zero Point Coder (ZPC) for persistent memory across AI coding sessions. All memory operations use the `agent-do zpc` CLI tool.

## Setup

```bash
agent-do zpc init
```

## Session Start

```bash
agent-do zpc status          # Memory state
agent-do zpc patterns        # Established conventions — follow these
```

## During Work

### Capture Lessons
When an error resolves, a correction occurs, or a convention is discovered:
```bash
agent-do zpc learn "context" "problem" "solution" "takeaway" --tags "tag1,tag2"
```

### Log Decisions
For architectural choices or trade-offs:
```bash
agent-do zpc decide "problem" --options "a,b,c" --chosen "b" --rationale "why" --confidence 0.8
```

### Search Memory
```bash
agent-do zpc query --tag mypy          # By tag
agent-do zpc query --type decisions    # All decisions
agent-do zpc query --text "docker"     # Free text
```

## After Work

```bash
agent-do zpc harvest                   # Consolidate lessons into patterns
```

## Multi-Agent

Include `agent-do zpc inject` output in spawned agent context.

Before reporting completion:
1. Log all error-resolution pairs
2. Log significant decisions
3. Include: "Lessons logged: N (new) | Decisions logged: N (new)"
